
<%=image_tag("/images/new_design/widget.png", :class => "widget_icon") %>
<div class="widget_header">
	<h5 class="get_widget">Get the Spot.Us Widget</h5> Want the embed code to add to your blog or site!? Grab the different widgets below.
</div>
<div class="widget_links">
	<a class="reveal_widget" href="#" rel="nofollow" style="text-decoration:underline;" onclick="slideWidget('simple_widget');return false;">SIMPLE WIDGET</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a class="reveal_widget" href="#" rel="nofollow" style="text-decoration:underline;" onclick="slideWidget('spotus_lite_widget');return false;">SPOT.US LITE</a>
</div>
<div class="widget_panel" id='simple_widget'>
	<div style="border:1px solid #888;margin:5px 0px 5px 0px;padding:0px;width:334px;">
		<iframe width='330' height='280' src='<%=pitch_path(@pitch)%>/widget' border='1' scrolling='no' noscroll></iframe>
	</div>
	<div class="widget_tip">To get this widget, just grab this html code and paste into your template.
		<textarea class="widget_code" style='width:320px;height:25px;'><%="<iframe width='330' src='#{pitch_path(@pitch,{:only_path=>false})}' border='1' scrolling='no' noscroll></iframe>"%></textarea>
		You can of course change the width of the iframe to fit your template.
	</div>
</div>

<div class="widget_panel" id='spotus_lite_widget'>
	<div class="widget_tip_lite">
		<h3>Spot.Us Lite</h3>
		<p><em>Spot.Us Lite</em> is widget which allows anyone to register at Spot.Us, login at Spot.Us and even donate to a pitch without having to leave the site hosting the widget. Isn't that cool?'</p>
		<p>You need to follow a few steps to get <em>Spot.Us Lite</em> working on your site. Just follow these simple steps below to get it up and running in no time.<p>
		<ol>
			<li>Download the file <a href='http://www.spot.us/helper.html' title='Grab the helper.html file' target='_blank'>http://www.spot.us/helper.html</a>, and upload it to your root folder on your server.</li>
			<li>Grab this html code and paste into your template:
			<textarea class="widget_code" style='width:300px;height:155px;'><%="<script type='text/javascript'> 						
var spotus_lite_host = 'http://www.domain.com/path'; // Example: If you can access the helper.html file at http://www.domain.com/path/helper.html, then you add http://www.domain.com/path there.
var spotus_lite_url = '#{pitch_path(@pitch,{:only_path=>false}).gsub('pitches','lite')}';
</script>
<script src='http://spot.us/javascripts/spotus_lite_min.js' type='text/javascript'></script>
<iframe width='300' src='' border='1' onChange='resizeIframe();' onLoad='resizeIframe();' id='spotus_lite' scrolling='no' noscroll></iframe>"
			%></textarea></li>	
			<li>You now need to modify the pasted code. You need to change <em>'http://www.domain.com/path'</em> to the root path of your server. Example: If you can access the helper.html file at http://www.domain.com/path/helper.html, then you add http://www.domain.com/path there.</li>					
		</ol>
		<p>You can of course change the width of the iframe to fit your template. Note: As Spot.Us Lite is an interactive widget, we recommend that you do not use widths below 300px.</p>
		<p>If you have any issues with the widget, please contact <a href='mailto:info@spot.us' title='info@spot.us'>info@spot.us</a></p>
	</div>
</div>